## Community Data Model

### User-Filled Fields

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Name | Display name of community |
| Description | Text description of goals and rules |
| Avatar | Community image (`avatarUrl`) |
| Cover | Background image (`coverImageUrl`) |
| Currency Name | Community currency labels (`settings.currencyNames`) |
| Type Tag | Community kind (`typeTag`, e.g. `team`, `future-vision`, `marathon-of-good`, `support`, `team-projects`, `political`, `housing`, `volunteer`, `corporate`, `custom`) |
| Hashtags | Community hashtag list (`hashtags`) |
| Hashtag Descriptions | Optional hashtag descriptions (`hashtagDescriptions`) |

**Implementation note:** Internal `typeTag: 'global'` exists in backend for `GLOBAL_COMMUNITY_ID`, but it is system-managed and not part of user-facing shared `CommunitySchema.typeTag` enum.

### System Fields

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| createdAt / updatedAt | Timestamps |
| members | Legacy member IDs list (current role source is `UserCommunityRole`) |
| isActive | Community active flag |
| isPriority | Priority flag used in sorting and global-merit logic |
| lastQuotaResetAt | Last quota reset timestamp |
| settings | Base settings block |
| permissionRules | Role/action allow/deny rules (custom overrides) |
| meritSettings / votingSettings / tappalkaSettings | Optional custom override blocks (effective values are merged with defaults at runtime) |
| linkedCurrencies | Optional linked currency IDs |

### Project communities (`isProject`)

- **Standard project:** `parentCommunityId` links to the parent team/community. Parent lead may receive a `project_created` notification when a different user creates the project under that parent.
- **Personal project:** `isPersonalProject === true`, no `parentCommunityId`; the logical owner is `founderUserId`. No parent-community notification on create. Invite links do not embed a parent team; accepting an invite adds the user only to the project, not to a parent community.

Full cooperative-project rules (Birzha `sourceEntityType === 'project'`, distribution, tickets): @business-projects.mdc.

### Community as actor (lead publishing)

Not a separate community **type** — a **mode** on `publications.create`:

| Input (tRPC / DTO) | Server behavior |
|--------------------|-----------------|
| `actingAsCommunityId` | If set: caller must be **lead** of that community (`userCommunityRoleService.getRole` → `role === 'lead'`). Field is **not** persisted; mapped to `sourceEntityId = actingAsCommunityId`, `sourceEntityType = 'community'`, then stripped from the create payload. |

Optional **`postCostFunding`** on create (when publishing as a community source to Birzha): `source_community_wallet` (default) debits **`postCost` from that community’s `CommunityWallet.balance`**; `caller_global_wallet` charges the caller’s global wallet instead.

**Withdraw** from a **МД** post that is a Birzha source post (`postCommunity.typeTag === 'marathon-of-good'` and publication has `sourceEntityType === 'community'` and `sourceEntityId`): caller must be **admin/lead of `sourceEntityId`** (same as project-source permission pattern); **author share** (after investor slice if any) is **`CommunityWallet.deposit(sourceEntityId, authorShare, 'publication_withdrawal')`** — merits accumulate on the **source community wallet**, not the user’s personal wallet. Details: @business-content.mdc, @business-merits.mdc.

